It’s Monday but it doesn’t have to be a bad thing. It’s all how you look at it and embrace it. 

Now onto the good stuff! 💜

First up thanks to influenster for the complimentary givenchybeauty concealer. Honestly it’s good stuff and I’m not just saying that cause it was free. I definitely would buy it. It’s my first 𝗠𝗨𝗦𝗧 𝗛𝗔𝗩𝗘. 

Second is the Toaster Bag from portlandleathcompany. This purple is perfect for Spring. If you aren’t a fan of big bags this one is the perfect size. In my opinion it is a 𝗠𝗨𝗦𝗧 𝗛𝗔𝗩𝗘. Plus check out the link in my bio for a direct link to this company. 

Third are these Eye Masks from sephora . I find that being an adult is stressful and hard. I don’t get nearby as much sleep as I should. These masks take away the puffiness and wake you up. They are a 𝗠𝗨𝗦𝗧 𝗛𝗔𝗩𝗘. 

Lastly this wouldn’t be Bookstagram without a book. This cozy mystery, Murder in a Scottish Shire is the March read for cozymysteryclub . I figured I get a head start. So this book is a 𝗠𝗨𝗦𝗧 𝗛𝗔𝗩𝗘 for March. 

Be sure to swipe ➡️ to see a close up of all the products. 

💬..QOTD..What is one of your 𝗠𝗨𝗦𝗧 𝗛𝗔𝗩𝗘𝗦 for this Monday?

grownalchemist 🤍

Grown Alchemist Hydra-Repair Day Cream is an exceptional product that deserves a glowing review. This luxurious cream is specifically designed to hydrate and nourish the skin, leaving it looking healthy, radiant, and youthful.

One of the most impressive aspects of this day cream is the high-quality ingredients that it contains. Grown Alchemist uses only the finest botanical extracts, vitamins, and antioxidants to create a formula that is both effective and gentle. The cream contains a powerful blend of camellia and rosehip oils, which work together to deeply moisturize and soothe the skin. These ingredients are also rich in antioxidants, which help to protect the skin against free radical damage and premature aging.

In addition to the nourishing oils, Grown Alchemist Hydra-Repair Day Cream also contains a range of other beneficial ingredients. These include antioxidant-rich aloe vera, collagen-boosting vitamin C, and skin-renewing wheatgerm extract. All of these ingredients work together to promote a healthy, youthful complexion.

What sets Grown Alchemist Hydra-Repair Day Cream apart from other moisturizers is its lightweight, non-greasy formula. The cream is easily absorbed into the skin, leaving it feeling soft and smooth without any oily residue. This makes it an ideal choice for daily use, as it provides all-day hydration without clogging pores or causing breakouts.

Overall, Grown Alchemist Hydra-Repair Day Cream is a fantastic product that delivers on its promises. Its high-quality ingredients, lightweight formula, and impressive results make it a top choice for anyone looking to improve the health and appearance of their skin. If you're in the market for a new day cream, this one is definitely worth a try.

Your social media feeds are not real life. You scroll and scroll and feel like everyone else has a better body, better skin, more money, a better house - it’s easy to feel like everyone else is always better and doing more.

We have no idea what goes on behind the scenes of the aesthetic pictures and videos we see online. We don’t see people’s skin up close, we don’t always spot photo editing.

It’s important to remember that social media isn’t reality, and, even if so - someone else having what you want or doing well for themselves, does NOT mean that you lack. We are so, so hard on ourselves. We forget that everyone’s journey is different.

Have grace for yourself today. Remember that quite literally no one on this planet is perfect. Perfection isn’t realistic, but loving yourself through the ups and downs of life and holding space for yourself to be human? Possible and very much worth it.

How’s your self love journey today? I encourage you to check in with yourself. ❤️

Aging skin.. most of us are experiencing it (unfortunately). This AM routine focuses on fortifying the skin barrier bc we all know that that’s the key to bouncy, glowing, youthful skin 💦

✨ paulaschoice Ultra-Gentle Cleanser* - Non-foaming cleanser that’s true to its name. Doesn’t leave the skin feeling squeaky clean, but it gets the job done.

✨ laneige_us Cream Skin Toner and Moisturizer - Milky goodness in a bottle. Wouldn’t say it replaces your moisturizer but it is super hydrating. Love how the texture is watery so I can pack on 2 layers without it feeling suffocating.

✨ paulaschoice Pro-Collagen Multi-Peptide Booster* - New in my skincare arsenal. It makes my skin so plump. Doesn’t pill and absorbs into the pores immediately too. Only qualm I have is that it has a vinegar scent, but luckily, it doesn’t linger.

✨ glowrecipe Guava Vitamin C Eye Cream* - Holy grail status AND a forever repurchase. It brightens, hydrates without feeling greasy, and preps the eye for makeup. Containing peptides, green caffeine, vitamin c, it is a true multitasker that literally targets all of your under-eye concerns.

✨ rovectin_us Lotus Cream* - Need a backup of this asap. The gel texture applies like silk on my skin. It’s not tacky and keeps my face moisturized all day. Definitely suitable for all skin types and all year round.

✨ skin1004official Hyalu-Cica Water Fit Sun Serum* - This chemical spf blends in like a dream. No white cast, eye sting, or pilling. I could skip out on moisturizer if I wanted to bc it’s THAT moisturizing. Would repurchase!

(*) = gifted

Monthly Recap — 
February was the first month in a LOOOOONG time where things felt normal and relaxed. Jacky and I are finally settling into married life and our new routine. 

We were able to travel to Lake Tahoe earlier in the month with some friends and got stuck in a snow storm… so that was fun lol The rest of the month consisted of date nights (watched Ant Man for Paul Rudd), meals with friends, and sushi bakes. 

I went to a memorial in February and it made me think about the legacy I want to leave behind, and how I hope people remember me when my time comes. Life really is so short.

The new Mehndi Moment Blush ($28) by the brand Kulfi.beauty just launched at the end of January sephora and I was one of the first to try it out! #gifted

There are 5 beautiful shades to choose from. The shade here is "Sandalwood Swirls' a neutral mauve color.

Key Ingredients:

🌷 Amla Extract- Rich in protective antioxidants to fight against free radicals

🌷 Hibiscus Extract- Boosts moisture and hydrates the skin

I have to say I am a big fan of cream products and this one knocked it out of the park. I fell in love with this blush the first time I applied it and the moment I felt its texture. In my opinion it is beginner proof for anyone who is just getting into cream products because it's very easy to blend but also it looks and feels so luxurious and makes the cheeks look perfectly flushed and healthy. It's a very lightweight, moussey texture and a little goes a long way in terms of pigment and application. The color might look intense but it doesn't have to be. I can go light-handed and it applies so effortlessly without separating the foundation underneath. There's no stickiness or too much shine just a beautiful application of color that lasts pretty much the whole day. I really like the shades and the one I have is perfect for me! I love the brand already and can't wait to try more from them.

Have you heard of this brand? The brand name, Kulfi, is a colorful and delicious South Asian ice cream 😋🍨 what a delightful name! It is a brand that donates to mental health organizations which I think is amazing! Check them out! Link is on my stories 🥰

Yesterday we had the privilege of furniture styling the makeupforever New HD Skin Powder Foundation Launch held at the sephora Pitt Street Shop. 
Hosted by emmachenartistry, the event was a combination of influencers, industry leaders and professional make-up artists.

Attendees also were able to have photo opportunities in our Blush Monika Sofas & Armchairs. The blush texture of our sofa brought a feminine touch to the space. 

The foundation of the event was to highlight the benefits of the New HD Skin Powder. The formula is a silky smooth powder that syncs with the skin to offer a 24-Hour comfortable wear and amazing finish. 

When we thought it couldn't get any better,  there was even a special performance from _cocojumbo who brought down the roof with her incredible range.

New from Fenty Skincare! Melt AWF Jelly 0il Makeup-Melting Cleanser!

This cleanser has a unique jelly texture that transforms upon application to the skin, becoming a lightweight oil. This cleanser breaks down longwear and water-proof makeup, sunscreen, dirt, oil, and impurities! That's a great range of products to mention. It shows that this makeup melting cleanser means business!
The cleanser has been created with a luxe blend of 9 oils to condition the skin while cleansing it. This product rinses quickly and easily... no residue left behind! That would be both disappointing and gross. 

It also hydrates, nourishes, and leaves skin feeling silky smooth.

Warning on the scent!!!
It has a light spa water-inspired scent from the natural oils in the formula. If you don't use products with fragrance, this may not be for you. However, I'm under the impression that the scent will be very light.

the Armani base >>>

#giftedbyarmani | I’m sure we’ve all collectively heard the hype around the armanibeauty Luminous Silk Foundation. I’m here to confirm: it is SO worth it!

I’ve been dealing with some closed comedones + red angry bumps (curtesy of my dermatitis ofc) and as a result, I try layering my foundation in attempts to get a smooth-looking base . . . but it just ends up looking cakey. Why am I saying this? Wellll, the Luminous Silk Foundation (shade 4.5) makes my skin texture look better with just one 1 pump! Did it make the irritation bumps disappear? Absolutely not because no makeup can do that. What it did do though was even out my skin tone and sink into my skin so seamlessly to where it overall looked smoother- it’s so hard to explain so iykyk 😩 I did some digging on the Armani Beauty website and they wrote that their micro–fil & trade technology creates that effect, so I probably have that to thank for what I was talking about!

Also, you guys all know I love to glow- tell me why I’ve never tried the Fluid Sheer Glow Enhancer (shade 2) until now?! It’s such a thin formula but it packs a punch in terms of glow, all while maintaining a natural glow-from-within quality. I don’t think I have to speak for it, just look at the glowy cheekbones 😩

It’s official, I’m now forever apart of the Armani Beauty fan club 🤍

Everything has to run smoothly on a set because "time is money," so you get an inside look at what actually works in the hair and beauty world - they don't have time to use crappy products. The day after the cat died (😭🐈), we all had super puffy eyes from crying. Azi needed to NOT look completely different from every other episode out of nowhere... so the makeup team cured the puffy eyes with these eye masks. 

Azi said they made him feel much better, so a few days later he asked to do the "luxurious" masks again just because they made his eyes feel so nice. I couldn't remember what they were but he said he thought they were something to do with Iceland. I gave him a pair from my own stash but apparently the ones I have on hand are not the quality he desires now that he's had the best 😅. A quick Google and sephoracanada search and we found what he was looking for. I was... surprised what the nice ones cost (heh) but they actually totally 100% worked so at least I know why...

So that is how we came to order skyniceland eye masks for our 9-year-old 😂😬

I strongly encourage beauty companies to sponsor HMU teams, because now you have a customer for life, and 9 is a pretty young age to start 🤣.

He is at school now so I think I will steal a pair for myself.

This week, we had the privilege of furniture styling the makeupforever New HD Skin Powder Foundation Launch held at the sephora Pitt Street Shop. 
Hosted by emmachenartistry, the event was a combination of influencers, industry leaders and professional make-up artists. 

Guests were treated to a palette of surprises! 💄 From having their faces professionally colour matched, to sharing makeup tips with fellow beauty experts, they weren't just captivated by the amazing product but also the decked out event space. 
Attendees also were able to have photo opportunities in our Blush Monika Sofas & Armchairs. The blush texture of our sofa brought a feminine touch to the space. 

The foundation of the event was to highlight the benefits of the New HD Skin Powder. The formula is a silky smooth powder that syncs with the skin to offer a 24-Hour comfortable wear and amazing finish. 

When we thought it couldn't get any better,  there was even a special performance from _cocojumbo who brought down the roof with her incredible range.

selflessbyhyram launched in June 2021 with sephora as its exclusive retail partner. It was unceremoniously dumped by the global retailer after only 18 months on the shelves. When this news broke, we assumed Selfless was on its way to the place where influencer and celebrity brands go to die.

But Gen-Z skin-fluencer hyram Yarbro refused to be broken and tossed aside by Sephora's notoriously fickle (and often misguided) marketers and merchandisers.

Selfless by Hyram, in a bold post-Sephora pivot, is moving to target - and lowering its product prices.

Yarbro, who has 6.5 million followers on TikTok, 4.55 million on YouTube, and 976,000 on Instagram, has always recommended "drugstore" skincare on his social platforms because that's where the majority of his followers shop. The new online and in-store partnership with Target (beginning February 5th) retails the formerly $16-$30 products for only $13-$24. Much more in line with Mass-market skincare brands like larocheposay, neutrogena, olay, and L'Oreal Revitalift. It also gives the brand additional exposure in the over 300 ultabeauty "Target" shop-in-shops, alongside naturiumskin, founded by fellow skin-fluencer susanyara.

Regarding the company's state, Yarbo said in an interview, "We're still charging full speed ahead...Target represents what I've always wanted the brand to be, which is more accessible." 

What do you think about this move? 
Will it save Selfless by Hyram?

Everything has to run smoothly on a set because "time is money," so you get an inside look at what actually works in the hair and beauty world - they don't have time to use crappy products. The day after the cat died (😭🐈), we all had super puffy eyes from crying. Azi needed to NOT look completely different from every other episode out of nowhere... so the makeup team cured the puffy eyes with these eye masks. 

Azi said they made him feel much better, so a few days later he asked to do the "luxurious" masks again just because they made his eyes feel so nice. I couldn't remember what they were but he said he thought they were something to do with Iceland. I gave him a pair from my own stash but apparently the ones I have on hand are not the quality he desires now that he's had the best 😅. A quick Google and sephoracanada search and we found what he was looking for. I was... surprised what the nice ones cost (heh) but they actually totally 100% worked so at least I know why...

So that is how we came to order skyniceland eye masks for our 9-year-old 😂😬

I strongly encourage beauty companies to sponsor HMU teams, because now you have a customer for life, and 9 is a pretty young age to start 🤣.

He is at school now so I think I will steal a pair for myself.
